description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within Northumberland Older Adults Community Treatment Team based in Hexham for a Clinical Support Assistant .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Older Adults Community Treatment Team aims to provide assessment, diagnosis, treatment based on a person centred approach for Older Adults who are experiencing mental health difficulties of both and organic of functional nature. This is often complicated due to age related changes, inclusive of psychical health difficulties. The post holder will be required to work collaboratively with services users families and carers to support the delivery of evidenced based interventions, inclusive of liaising with many different support services including local authority and our voluntary sector. A good understanding of the geographic nature of Northumberland would be helpful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team are looking to recruit an individual that is dynamic, motivated and must demonstrate excellent communication and interpersonal skills. It is important they have previous experience working with individuals with mental health difficulties and how this pertains to Older Adults.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will offer the successful candidate the opportunity to develop their skills and knowledge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Gary Collis  Job title: Clinical Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: gary.collis@cntw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jo Rowsell, Pathway Manager joanne.rowsell@cntw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
